  "_meta": {
    "tagline": "Stat lines in, standings out \u2014 the league's scoring rules are the DAG.",
    "motif": "default",
    "motif_palette": {
      "primary": "#1a472a",
      "accent": "#f0b21f",
      "ink": "#0a1a10"
    },
    "description_rich": "Fantasy Football is a four-hop DAG: raw weekly stat lines for 18 NFL players feed into rosters through a `RosterAssignments` join table, the rosters aggregate yardage and touchdowns and re-apply the league's scoring formula at the team level, matchups look up each side's roster score to declare a winner, and the standings rank everyone for playoff seeding. The interesting thing isn't the data \u2014 it's that *every scoring rule lives in the rulebook*. Change `1 point per 25 passing yards` to `1 per 20`, rebuild, and every player, every roster, every matchup result, and every playoff seed re-derives identically in Postgres, Python, Excel, and OWL.",
    "use_cases": [
      "**Re-tune the scoring formula.** Edit `Players.ProjectedScore` from `PassingYards/25` to `PassingYards/20` (a more generous QB rule) \u2014 every player, every roster total, every matchup margin, and every standing recomputes from a single change.",
      "**Run a what-if trade.** Move *Travis Kelce* from `mahomes-mob` to `hurts-limit` by editing a `RosterAssignments` row \u2014 Mahomes Mob's `ProjectedScore` drops by Kelce's contribution, Hurts Limit's jumps, and any matchup either roster plays this week flips its `Winner` if the margin crosses zero.",
      "**Switch to PPR (point-per-reception) scoring.** Add `+ {{Receptions}}` to the per-player scoring formula and watch high-volume WRs (Hill, Adams, Diggs) leapfrog their roster's QB in fantasy value without touching any other field.",
      "**Ask the same question in four substrates.** *\"Which roster is on track to win Week 1 by the largest margin?\"* \u2014 run it as a SQL `ORDER BY ABS(margin) DESC LIMIT 1` against the Postgres view, as a Python list-comprehension over the Matchups module, or as an Excel sort \u2014 same answer, no glue code.",
      "**Add a 7th roster mid-season.** Insert one row in `Rosters` and three in `RosterAssignments`; the new team's `ProjectedScore` is computed from the rulebook the instant the rows land \u2014 no \"recompute standings\" job to run."
    ],
